text.section:
An entity subject to this section shall provide coverage for a refill of prescription eye drops:
in accordance with guidance for early refills of topical ophthalmic products provided to Medicare Part D plan sponsors by the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services; and
if:
the prescribing health care practitioner indicates on the original prescription that additional quantities of the prescription eye drops are needed;
the refill requested by the insured does not exceed the number of additional quantities indicated on the original prescription by the prescribing health care practitioner; and
the prescription eye drops prescribed by the health care practitioner are a covered benefit under the policy or contract of the insured.
